================================================================================
fragc
================================================================================

fragc is a tiny ShaderToy-like program in C for writing pixel shaders that run
on the CPU. You write a function that fulfills the frag() interface in a .c or
.cpp file and the processed image is displayed.

This program will only work on Windows 11.

BUILDING
--------

Blank buffer:
	$ run_app.bat

Image process:
	$ app_run.bat <image path>

Image process with shader:
	$ app_run.bat <image path> <shader path>

If a shader path isn't specific, the default shader fill will be loaded. It is ./src/shaders/main.c.

Images are output into ./target/output.png by default.

HOT-LOADING
-----------

Pressing 'R' will re-load the current selected instantly.

If the shader file's metadata changes, it will automatically be recompiled and
reloaded.

C++ OVERLOADS
-------------

The whole project should be able to be compiled with either clang or clang++
to allow the shaders to be written with +, -, *, / overloads for the vector and
matrix types. This makes writing the shaders more convenient and more similar to
writing GLSL.

SHADER UNIFORMS
---------------

Shaders must follow the function signature:
	typedef Vec4 (*FragFn)(const Uniform *uniform, const Sampler *sampler, Vec2 uv);

The shader entry point must be named 'frag' so that the LibLoader can find it.

Shaders will take:
	typedef struct uniform_t {
	    f32 elapsed_time;    // frame-time elapsed in seconds
	    i32 vp_width;        // viewport width
	    i32 vp_height;       // viewport height
	    Vec4 mouse_pos;      // .zw if mouse is clicked, .xy otherwise
	    usize sampler_count; // Number of textures *sampler points to
	} Uniform;

